Singer and TV personality, Unathi Nkayi has taken some time out to frolic on the sandy beaches of the gorgeous Zanzibar islands. The Idols SA judges spent couple of days there with a few loved ones in Tanzania. While there, the star spent most of her time in sexy bikinis, she swam with dolphins, ate some good food and got in some good old fashioned down time. In one of her post, Unathi expressed that swimming with dolphins was a bucket list item for her and she is seemed very happy to check it off her list. “TODAY was unbelievable my friend. God was in charge and wanted us to TRULY enjoy this #BucketList Woaw! We swam with dolphins,” she said in another post. She also took some time to see some the flora and fauna of Zanzibar when she visited the forest at the Jozani-Chwaka Bay National Park. She is currently on her way back to South Africa. Check out the snaps below: Evening swims and melted ice coz Zanzibar is SO HOT?? A post shared by  Unathi.Africa (@unathi.co) on Oct 18, 2018 at 10:04am PDT  #BucketList we swam with dolphins????Look at God A post shared by  Unathi.Africa (@unathi.co) on Oct 19, 2018 at 4:38am PDT  TODAY was unbelievable my friend. God was in charge and wanted us to TRULY enjoy this #BucketList Woaw! We swam with dolphins?? A post shared by  Unathi.Africa (@unathi.co) on Oct 19, 2018 at 4:52am PDT  Then we visited the forest at the Jozani-Chwaka Bay National Park?? A post shared by  Unathi.Africa (@unathi.co) on Oct 19, 2018 at 6:36am PDT  And then we went on a sunset cruise ?? A post shared by  Unathi.Africa (@unathi.co) on Oct 19, 2018 at 10:33am PDT  Zanzibar I LOVE you?? A post shared by  Unathi.Africa (@unathi.co) on Oct 20, 2018 at 1:23am PDT   